# rm(list = ls())

# oddsp(x_i,)
odds <- function(x, beta){
  expo <- exp(x %*% beta)
  return(expo/(1+expo))
}

# , NX1X2betatrue parameterR
NRiter <- function(N, beta, R){
  best <- matrix(nrow = R,ncol = length(beta))   # R
  for(r in 1:R){
    ones <- rep(1, N)
    X1 <- rnorm(N)
    X2 <- rnorm(N)
    X <- matrix(c(ones, X1, X2), ncol = 3)
    y <- odds(X, beta)     # y,Y=1
    bold <- c(0,0,0)
    while(1){                # Newton-Raphson Algorithm ,
      pro <- odds(X, bold)
      W <- diag(c(pro*(1-pro)))
      Wi <- solve(t(X) %*% W %*% X)
      bnew <- bold + Wi %*% t(X) %*% (y - pro)
      if(max(abs(bnew-bold)) < 1e-5){break}
      bold <- bnew
    }
    best[r,] <- bold
  }
  return(best)
}

# N=2005008001000
